a:2:{s:7:"content";s:1136:"<h2>Beauty Technology: Designing Seamless Interfaces for Wearable Computing</h2>
<h3>By Katia Vega,Hugo Fuks</h3>
<p>By using the body's surface as an interactive platform, the integration of technology into beauty products is explored and can be applied directly to ones skin, fingernails, and hair adding new functionality to beauty products using technology in a personal, seamless and fashionable way. An interdisciplinary approach is taken, exploring the design of Beauty Technologies such as Conductive Makeup, Tech Nails, Hairware and FX e-makeup in order to create novel interfaces for Human Computer Interaction and Cyborg Fashion.</p>
<p><strong>Publication Date:</strong> 2016</p>
<p><strong>Expertise Level:</strong> Beginner,Intermediate</p>
<p><strong>Intended Audience:</strong> General,College/University</p>
<p><strong>ISBN:</strong> 978-3319157610</p>
